13/01/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish, US and Iraqi officials held trilateral talks in Ankara this week. 
Afterwards, Iraqi Deputy Foreign Minister Hamid al-Bayati said the three sides had laid the groundwork for long-term co-operation in ending the terrorist threat in Iraq.
Also Wednesday, Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan returned from an official visit to Moscow. 
He and Russian President Vladimir Putin agreed on a number of issues related to bilateral co-operation. 
(NTV, Anadolu Agency, TurkishPress.com, AFX - 12/01/05)
